  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version (output of `vyper --version`): 0.3.2\r\n* OS: linux\r\n* Python Version (output of `python --version`): 3.10.2\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nVyper external test error: \"vyper.exceptions.VyperException: Compilation failed with the following errors:\\n\\nTypeMismatch: method_id must be a 4-byte hex literal or Bytes[4], like method_id=0x12345678 or method_id=method_id(\\\"foo()\\\") \\nvyper.ast.nodes.Name:\\n      9     x: Bytes[4] = b\\\"\\\\x12\\\\x34\\\\x56\\\\x78\\\"\\n---> 10     return _abi_encode(\\\"abc\\\", method_id=x)\\n------------------------------------------------^\\n     11\\n\\n\\nTypeMismatch: method_id must be a 4-byte hex literal or Bytes[4], like method_id=0x12345678 or method_id=method_id(\\\"foo()\\\") \\nvyper.ast.nodes.Name:\\n     15     x: Bytes[4] = b\\\"\\\\x12\\\\x34\\\\x56\\\\x78\\\"\\n---> 16     return _abi_encode(115792089237316195423570985008687907853269984665640564039457584007913129639935, method_id=x)\\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------^\\n     17\\n\\n\\nTypeMismatch: method_id must be a 4-byte hex literal or Bytes[4], like method_id=0x12345678 or method_id=method_id(\\\"foo()\\\") \\nvyper.ast.nodes.Name:\\n     30     s.c = convert(0x1234, uint16)\\n---> 31     return _abi_encode(115792089237316195423570985008687907853269984665640564039457584007913129639935, s, convert(3, uint256), method_id=x)\\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------^\\n     32\\n\\n\\n[18477] Failed to execute script 'vyper_compile' due to unhandled exception!\\n\"\r\n\r\n@charles-cooper sorry for the unformatted error. I think you'll get the point :)\r\n\r\n```\r\n@external\r\n@pure\r\ndef f1() -> Bytes[100]:\r\n    return _abi_encode(\"abc\", method_id=0x12345678)\r\n\r\n@external\r\n@pure\r\ndef f2() -> Bytes[100]:\r\n    x: Bytes[4] = b\"\\x12\\x34\\x56\\x78\"\r\n    return _abi_encode(\"abc\", method_id=x)\r\n\r\n@external\r\n@pure\r\ndef f3() -> Bytes[100]:\r\n    x: Bytes[4] = b\"\\x12\\x34\\x56\\x78\"\r\n    return _abi_encode(115792089237316195423570985008687907853269984665640564039457584007913129639935, method_id=x)\r\n\r\n```\r\n",
