    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "I believe f2() and f3() are failing because `_abi_encode` expects `method_id` to be an inline literal or constant. you could make them work by declaring `x` as a module-level constant, e.g.\r\n```vyper\r\nMETHOD_ID: constant(Bytes[4]) = b\"\\x12\\x34\\x56\\x78\"\r\n@external\r\n@pure \r\ndef f2() -> Bytes[100]:\r\n    return _abi_encode(\"abc\", method_id=METHOD_ID)\r\n```",
